5000|$|After {{years of}} {{research}} and design refinements, <b>Technogel</b> also launched its first line of consumer products in 2008 as the <b>Technogel</b> Sleeping brand of gel mattresses and pillows. The <b>Technogel</b> Sleeping collection is sold through various licensees and retailers in more than 50 countries. A number of athletes use <b>Technogel</b> products for rejuvenating and restorative support required for peak performance.|$|E
50|$|<b>Technogel</b> is a {{multinational}} corporation with primary manufacturing operations in Italy and Germany and an administrative {{headquarters in the}} United States in Pittsburgh. Established in 2010, Technogel’s US branch focuses on the development and sales of <b>Technogel</b> Sleeping products, {{as well as new}} innovations in comfort that reach consumers with the quality and reputation of the <b>Technogel</b> brand name.|$|E
5000|$|Initially {{developed}} and patented by Bayer Material Science, and now licensed exclusively by the <b>Technogel</b> company, <b>Technogel</b> is a polyurethane gel made without plasticizer oils; it's odorless, non-toxic, biocompatible and durable.|$|E
50|$|In 2013, the <b>Technogel</b> Sleeping VIVE line {{of luxury}} gel {{mattresses}} and pillows and the <b>Technogel</b> Living seating supports collection were both launched. And the company continues {{research and development}} and new product releases.|$|E
5000|$|<b>Technogel</b> {{dates back}} to 1990 in Italy, when Massimo Losio--also an {{executive}} of Selle Royal Group--founded Royal Medica to use the patented gel material to relieve the discomfort of individuals bound to wheelchairs and hospital beds. By the mid-90s, Royal Medica had expanded into office furniture, providing applications of <b>Technogel</b> for seat cushions, armrests & ergonomic desk accessories. In 1998, Royal Medica formed {{a joint venture with}} Otto Bock--the partnership took the namesake of the material and gave rise to the company now known as <b>Technogel.</b>|$|E
50|$|<b>Technogel</b> Italia S.r.l. is a {{manufacturing}} {{company based in}} Vicenza, Italy.|$|E
5000|$|Continuing {{to expand}} its applications, <b>Technogel</b> {{has become one of}} the world's leading {{producers}} of gel. It is positioned as a wellness company, known for creating sleeping and lifestyle products that blend gel technology with high-end design to make the world more comfortable.|$|E
5000|$|<b>Technogel</b> {{combines}} the adaptability and 3D deformation of a fluid with {{the stability of}} a solid to offer comfortable, supportive cushioning. It's also known for its cooling effect: the material's high conductivity provides thermal regulation that can create a fresh, cool feeling and help avoid overheating.|$|E
